<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>
A triangular piece of land has sides measuring <m>{18}</m> m, <m>{21}</m> m, and <m>{29}</m> m. Find the area of the land using Heron’s formula.
</p>



<p>
Give your answer correct to <alert>2 decimal places</alert>.
</p>

<p>
Area = <fillin characters="8" name="ans1"/> <m>\text{ cm}^2</m>  
</p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
The sides of the triangle are <m>{18}</m> cm, <m>{21}</m> cm and <m>{29}</m> cm.
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Find the semi-perimeter.
</p>

<p>
<me>
s = \frac{a+b+c}{2}
</me>
</p>

<p>
<me>
s = \frac{{18}+{21}+{29}}{2}
</me>
</p>

<p>
<me>
s = {34}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Write Heron’s formula.
</p>

<p>
<me>
A=\sqrt{s(s-a)(s-b)(s-c)}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 3: Substitute the values.
</p>

<p>
<me>
A=\sqrt{{34}({34}-{18})({34}-{21})({34}-{29})}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 4: Simplify the brackets.
</p>

<p>
<me>
A=\sqrt{{34}\times {16}\times {13}\times {5}}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 5: Evaluate the square root.
</p>

<p>
<me>
A \approx {188.04}\text{ cm}^2
</me>
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the area of the triangle is:
</p>

<p>
<me>
Area = {{188.04}\text{ cm}^2}
</me>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>188.04</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>